# Git Commit Messages — English Only

All git commit messages (subject and body) must be written in **English**, even when communicating with the user in French.

## Format

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

- `feat:` — new feature
- `fix:` — bug fix
- `docs:` — documentation only
- `refactor:` — code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
- `test:` — adding or updating tests
- `chore:` — maintenance, tooling, deps

## Examples

```
feat: allow public room browsing without login

Enable catalog, floor plan, and room detail pages for visitors.
Reservation submission still requires authentication.
```

```
fix: restore mobile navigation menu on small screens

Add hamburger drawer for nav links hidden below the lg breakpoint.
```

## Do not

- Write commit subjects or bodies in French
- Mix languages in the same commit message
